snippet.textDisplay: I'm a self-employed, sole proprietor, building custom acoustic guitars for a living. Four of my clients for this year decided to cancel their build projects, which to me represents about $30,000 in lost income. And as far as I know, the only relief I can look forward to is that $1200, one-time check. Great. That will almost cover one month's rent. I guess after that's gone, I'll have to eat grass and tree bark, and sleep under a log.
